<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5116.3.5>
    bibo:endPage "409" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2022-03-21" ;
    bibo:startPage "393" ;
    bibo:volume "5116" ;
    dc:creator "Hanafi, Norhafiz; Chen, Meng-Hsien; Seah, Ying Giat; Chang, Chih-Wei; Liu, Shang Yin Vanson; Chao, Ning Labbish" ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "Johnius sasakii, a new species of croaker (Perciformes: Sciaenidae) with a key to Johnius from East Malaysia, Borneo" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372228>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372230>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372232>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372234>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372238>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372240>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372242> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372228>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Holotype of Johnius sasakii sp. nov., (A) Fresh specimen, (B) preserved specimen, NMMB-P 34733, 111 mm SL, Bako, Sarawak, Malaysia, 17 March 2017, collected by Norhafiz Hanafi, fish market." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6372228/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372230>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. First gill arch on left side of Johnius sasakii sp. nov. (paratype: NMMB-P 34739, 146 mm SL)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6372230/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372232>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Swimbladder of Johnius sasakii sp. nov. (paratype, NMMB-P 34739, 146 mm SL), with 14 pairs of lateral appendages followed by a hammer-shape, with a number of arborescent appendages along the entire lateral surface (ventral view)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6372232/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372234>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Inner surface of sagitta of Johnius sasakii sp. nov., paratype, NMMB-P 34739, 146 mm SL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6372234/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372238>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Photographs of the comparative materials. (A) Johnius sasakii sp. nov.; NMMB-P 34738, paratype, 114 mm SL, (B) Johnius heterolepis NMMB-P 35556, 105 mm SL, (C) Johnius carouna, NMMB-P 34743 141 mm SL and (D) Johnius macrorhynus; NMMB-P 34744, 116 mm SL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6372238/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372240>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Phylogenetic trees reconstructed using the mtDNA 16S genes of five Johnius (Johnius) species. Values above the branches are respective bootstrap values from 5000 replications for the Neighbour-Joining (NJ) and Maximum-Likelihood (ML) analyses. Bar indicates genetic distances of 0.02." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6372240/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6372242>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. (A) Phylogenetic trees reconstructed using the nDNA S7 genes of 5 Johnius (Johnius) species. Values above the branches are respective bootstrap values from 5000 replications for the Neighbour-Joining (NJ) and Maximum-Likelihood (ML) analyses. Bar indicates genetic distances of 0.02. (B) Three nucleotide differences (black arrow) at the sites 215, 308, and 354 nucleotides in the homozygote nuclear gene S7 of J. sasakii sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6372242/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

